    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, those are good foundational points. my students specifically want to dive deeper into the economic argument. some people argue that strict enforcement actually helps the domestic workforce by preventing wage suppression. could you expand on that from a more technical or economic standpoint? like, how would a debater frame the connection between border control and protecting low-skilled worker wages?",
