      "content": "Strict enforcement protects domestic wages by eliminating the \"race to the bottom\" where employers illegally hire undocumented workers at submarket rates just to undercut legal competitors. By closing this loophole, we force all labor to pay fair market wages, which boosts the purchasing power of American workers and stimulates the broader economy. Furthermore, enforcing the law allows the government to collect necessary taxes and fees on all labor, ensuring a fair distribution of revenue that funds public services for everyone. This approach creates a level playing field where businesses compete on innovation and efficiency rather than on the ability to exploit cheap, illegal labor.",
